adjectives.description: testaceous (comparative more testaceous, superlative most testaceous)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Pertaining to earthenware or baked clay.
examples: [T]hey were burnt, or only baked in Oven or Sunne: According to the ancient way, in many bricks, tiles, pots, and testaceous works […].

entries.meaning: Having a shell, especially one which is not articulated.
examples: It has a very large head, in proportion to its body, all covered with a shell, like other testaceous Animals […].

entries.meaning: Of a dull orange or brownish colour, like brick.
